06:17.111 --> 06:18.610
         The dumb ones.         

06:20.180 --> 06:22.513
      No fuck-ups. Alright?     

06:22.549 --> 06:25.317
  I'm not spending the rest of  
    my life in a concrete box   

06:25.352 --> 06:28.053
         simply because         
  you couldn't stick to a plan. 

06:28.122 --> 06:29.688
           Understood?          

06:30.556 --> 06:32.891
    Now, let's get this done.   

06:40.133 --> 06:45.070
  But know this. Once you step  
     inside here, you're in.    

06:45.138 --> 06:47.405
   No more of this pussy shit.  

06:47.407 --> 06:49.407
        Mate, we do this        
       together, alright?       

06:49.409 --> 06:51.242
        The way Dad would       
          have wanted.          

06:51.311 --> 06:54.012
       And what we start,       
       we're gonna finish.      

07:00.754 --> 07:01.753
               OK.              

07:01.821 --> 07:03.655
        Now, I know we're       
     wearing gloves, but try    

07:03.690 --> 07:05.690
      not to touch anything     
       you don't have to.       

07:06.926 --> 07:08.059
       Can I take a seat?       

07:09.829 --> 07:11.763
          You're clean.         
          You can sit.          

07:14.401 --> 07:15.767
               OK.              

07:21.175 --> 07:23.441
         Alright. So...         

07:23.443 --> 07:25.543
         Rodger will be         
         here about 5:30        

07:25.579 --> 07:28.213
      tonight to brush and      
         reshoe Freddie.        

07:28.248 --> 07:29.847
 The buyer will turn up at 7:00.

07:29.883 --> 07:31.950
   I've mapped everything out   
        so we'll be ready       

07:31.952 --> 07:34.619
  about half an hour to an hour 
     before Rodger turns up.    

07:35.589 --> 07:38.290
     Wh... why is this buyer    
        coming at 7pm to        

07:38.358 --> 07:40.624
       try and put Freddie      
       into a horse float?      

07:40.693 --> 07:42.760
       What kind of idiot       
   loads a horse in the dark?   

07:42.795 --> 07:45.130
   I... I reckon Freddie will   
     get spooked, don't you?    

07:45.132 --> 07:45.963
        Not our concern.        

07:46.800 --> 07:48.767
     Rodger organised it and    
     he's with Mum all day.     

07:48.802 --> 07:51.102
     Besides, mate, it works    
 beautifully with our schedule. 

07:51.137 --> 07:53.138
      The chances of anyone     
    seeing us leave at night    

07:53.140 --> 07:56.408
is the same as when we came here
this morning - minimal at best. 

07:56.910 --> 07:59.944
      Now, you'll see that      
       I've set the alarm       

07:59.980 --> 08:03.281
     for final idiot checks     
        and exit - 6:15.        

08:03.317 --> 08:05.149
        You know, I still       
        don't understand        

08:05.218 --> 08:07.085
       why we're here for       
         the whole day.         

08:07.988 --> 08:09.453
        Because there's a       
         lot to prepare.        

08:10.156 --> 08:12.657
 And we're only gonna have half 
  an hour or so to deal with... 

08:13.260 --> 08:14.726
      to deal with Rodger.      

08:14.761 --> 08:15.994
         And what's with        
        all the cleaning?       

08:15.996 --> 08:17.795
        You've got, like,       
      seven cleans in here.     

08:17.831 --> 08:18.729
           [Jeff] Six.          

08:18.765 --> 08:20.564
      Mate, human emotions      
      being what they are,      

08:20.600 --> 08:22.667
    if we leave the cleaning    
      till after the fact,      

08:22.669 --> 08:24.569
 we're likely to miss something.

08:24.604 --> 08:25.836
      I think you're gonna      
          be surprised,         

08:25.905 --> 08:27.572
       Terry, how quickly       
       the day's gonna go.      

08:27.608 --> 08:29.674
    - There's a lot to cover.   
      - Oh, I can see that.     

08:30.077 --> 08:33.678
And a lot of this stuff, I don't
  remember us ever discussing.  

08:33.679 --> 08:36.480
       These other things       
        you've got - "ice       

08:36.515 --> 08:39.683
       junkie rehearsal",       
       "electrocution"...       

08:40.153 --> 08:41.485
              Tez.              

08:41.520 --> 08:43.522
       Terry, look at me.       

08:44.491 --> 08:46.324
    As Dad would always say,    

08:46.359 --> 08:50.294
       failing to plan is       
        planning to fail.       

08:50.330 --> 08:51.863
       I know that, Jeff.       

08:51.865 --> 08:53.798
       It's just a little       
         intense seeing         

08:53.834 --> 08:55.634
         it all written         
         down like this.        

08:55.669 --> 08:57.802
         You've done it         
       like a to-do list.       

08:57.838 --> 09:00.705
       It is a to-do list.      
   That's exactly what it is.   

09:00.774 --> 09:02.373
     You know what? Just...     
        just forget this.       

09:02.442 --> 09:03.942
           Let's just           
      keep moving, can we?      

09:03.977 --> 09:08.446
          Alright. OK.          
   Let's synchronise watches.   

09:08.481 --> 09:10.381
           Seriously?           

09:10.450 --> 09:12.283
I'm very serious. No short cuts.

09:12.318 --> 09:14.885
Yeah, but couldn't you have just
 said, "What time do you have?" 

09:14.954 --> 09:16.721
    instead of, "Synchronise    
      our fucking watches"?     

09:17.524 --> 09:19.023
 Alright, what time do you have?

09:19.058 --> 09:19.858
            I don't.            

09:20.727 --> 09:22.994
       Because, like most       
      normal human beings,      

09:23.029 --> 09:25.696
        I use my phone to       
        tell me the time.       

09:25.731 --> 09:28.233
      But you've taken that     
       from me, remember?       

10:06.706 --> 10:09.074
       [metal box clunks]       

11:01.661 --> 11:03.160
            Find it?            

11:03.162 --> 11:04.663
              Yeah.             

11:05.598 --> 11:07.098
        We'll have to put       
       it back afterwards,      

11:07.133 --> 11:08.933
       so I'll make a note      
         in the agenda.         

11:11.405 --> 11:12.671
          Doesn't work.         

11:13.339 --> 11:15.006
     Wind it. Give it a tap.    

11:16.109 --> 11:18.642
         Dad used to say        
  it had a heart for a battery. 

11:18.678 --> 11:20.812
         Give it enough         
     attention, it'll work.     

11:25.452 --> 11:26.851
          [watch ticks]         

11:26.920 --> 11:28.019
              Huh!              

11:31.424 --> 11:33.024
          What's that?          

11:34.127 --> 11:35.126
           Toothache.           

11:36.195 --> 11:40.598
   Alright. Let's synchronise   
        watches for 7:14.       

11:40.633 --> 11:41.800
     It's time to ring Mum.     

11:42.802 --> 11:45.269
       [car horns honk, PA      
     announcements on tape]     

11:45.305 --> 11:46.771
             [dials]            

11:50.877 --> 11:53.878
         Hey. It's Jeff.        

11:53.880 --> 11:56.447
   Jeff, Mum. Your son. Jeff.   

11:56.483 --> 11:59.050
    [laughs] Yeah. Yes, yeah.   

11:59.119 --> 12:01.218
    - No, we've just arrived.   
   - [train station PA chimes]  

12:01.220 --> 12:03.888
    No, it's great. It's good   
  to spend some time together.  

12:03.890 --> 12:06.891
     Big city, Sydney. Very     
        loud, very noisy.       

12:06.893 --> 12:09.027
    [car horns honk on tape]    

12:09.696 --> 12:11.396
   Oh, no, he's off shopping.   

12:12.532 --> 12:13.965
       Of course he wants       
      to talk to you, Mum.      

12:14.000 --> 12:15.566
        He's out... he's        
       buying chocolate...      

12:15.568 --> 12:17.501
       chocolates for the       
       kids or something.       

12:17.536 --> 12:19.404
  No, no, Jeff. Not chocolate.  

12:19.406 --> 12:20.738
         Sorry, hang...         

12:20.740 --> 12:22.974
         Not chocolate.         
  The boys don't eat chocolate. 

12:23.009 --> 12:24.141
              What?             

12:24.177 --> 12:26.577
     - Sue doesn't allow it.    
      - You're shittin' me!     

12:26.579 --> 12:28.913
When Mum sent the boys chocolate
           at Easter,           

12:28.915 --> 12:31.749
    Sue spent a whole night,    
    and I begged her not to,    

12:31.751 --> 12:34.152
       but she wrote this       
        three-page essay        

12:34.187 --> 12:36.253
     on the negative impact     
      of chocolate on kids.     

12:36.322 --> 12:40.191
    Don't ask me what it is.    
   I don't get it. But Mum...   

12:40.227 --> 12:42.927
      Trust me, Mum knows.      
   They can't have chocolate.   

12:43.763 --> 12:46.263
         You there? Mum?        

12:46.332 --> 12:47.832
      No, you misheard me.      

12:47.867 --> 12:50.901
  No, no, no, he's buying them  
    for my... for... for me.    

12:50.936 --> 12:52.771
      H-h-how's your blood?     

12:53.907 --> 12:56.775
     Your blood levels, Mum.    
    The markers, are they up?   

12:57.777 --> 12:59.944
       OK, well, what did       
         the doctor say?        

13:00.613 --> 13:01.912
        Yeah, no, I kn...       

13:01.948 --> 13:03.448
       No... I hope you're      
         not calling him        

13:03.450 --> 13:04.715
        "Dr Vindaloo" to        
         his face, Mum.         

13:04.751 --> 13:05.450
     He's there to help you.    

13:06.520 --> 13:08.286
       Alright, and so...       
         and the chemo?         

13:09.121 --> 13:10.555
     That's happening today?    

13:11.857 --> 13:14.392
  A-a-and wh-what about Rodger? 

13:15.428 --> 13:17.795
      Well, is he... is he      
      staying back with you     

13:17.797 --> 13:20.799
    or is he still seeing...    
     the guy about Freddie?     

13:21.300 --> 13:23.267
       Freddie the horse.       

13:23.302 --> 13:24.969
         The horse, Mum!        

13:27.740 --> 13:29.473
    Right. Right. Well, good.   

13:29.475 --> 13:30.875
    So, happy thoughts, hey?    

13:31.711 --> 13:34.479
         For the chemo.         
       Positive thinking.       

13:34.981 --> 13:35.980
              Yes.              

13:36.649 --> 13:38.917
    Alright. I love you, Mum.   

13:40.287 --> 13:41.752
          Mum? I said--         

13:41.787 --> 13:44.255
    [car horns honk on tape]    

13:44.824 --> 13:46.224
     Yeah, man. We're good.     

13:46.993 --> 13:49.961
 Rodger's gonna be here at 5:30.

13:51.263 --> 13:52.330
     You're sure sat phones     
        can't be traced?        

13:53.933 --> 13:56.434
 Yes, mate. It's half the reason
      why people buy them.      

13:57.837 --> 13:59.837
        Are you confident       
  our phones made it to Sydney? 

14:00.773 --> 14:03.140
  The courier company will send 
   the package back on Monday   

14:03.175 --> 14:04.842
        and the GPS will        
      show that our phones      

14:04.844 --> 14:06.443
         had a glorious         
       weekend in Sydney.       

14:06.479 --> 14:07.678
           We're good.          

14:07.680 --> 14:09.113
            Alright.            

14:30.637 --> 14:32.169
         [Terry] What is        
       there to rehearse?       

14:32.204 --> 14:33.871
       Rodger goes in the       
         bath, appliance        

14:33.940 --> 14:35.540
        goes in the bath,       
          end of story.         

14:35.608 --> 14:37.542
  When do we put the water in?  

14:37.610 --> 14:39.543
    Well, before, obviously.    

14:39.612 --> 14:40.979
         OK, me or you?         

14:41.347 --> 14:42.380
             Either.            

14:43.616 --> 14:45.149
    Now or closer to the act?   

14:45.785 --> 14:47.150
     I don't know. Whenever.    

14:47.186 --> 14:49.353
  And what appliance do we use? 

14:49.389 --> 14:50.687
           Hair dryer.          

14:50.723 --> 14:52.023
        She doesn't have        
          a hair dryer          

14:52.058 --> 14:53.557
      anymore. She smashed      
          it, remember?         

14:53.626 --> 14:55.826
    She's got no fucking hair   
     on her head. The chemo!    

14:55.862 --> 14:57.228
     [sighs] Then a toaster.    

14:58.331 --> 15:00.231
        They use the oven       
       grill to do toast!       

15:00.233 --> 15:01.666
       Rodger thinks it's       
          crispier that         

15:01.701 --> 15:03.000
        way. Come on, you       
         know this shit.        

15:03.035 --> 15:05.236
       Well, obviously you      
        have the answer.        

15:09.142 --> 15:11.876
        He kills himself        
        with a Tasman X?        

15:11.911 --> 15:13.511
         Yeah. Why not?         

15:13.546 --> 15:15.880
   I don't know. It's got some  
   poetry about it, I suppose.  

15:15.916 --> 15:18.082
  Poetry? Mate, this is serious 
         fucking pathos.        

15:18.151 --> 15:20.551
     This is Rodger's first     
      and favourite radio.      

15:20.587 --> 15:22.386
Alright. Great. So, are we done?

15:22.421 --> 15:25.189
   No. Cord's not gonna reach   
  from the hallway to the bath. 

15:26.059 --> 15:27.392
   So grab an extension lead.   

15:28.094 --> 15:31.195
  No, no. Not those. That one.  

15:31.764 --> 15:33.097
     One of Dad's old ones?     

15:33.166 --> 15:36.100
       Mm-hm. More poetry.      

15:36.169 --> 15:38.035
        Oh, yeah, no, you       
      should write fucking      

15:38.071 --> 15:39.604
         Christmas cards        
          for Hallmark.         

15:44.076 --> 15:45.776
[Jeff] No, uh, don't touch that.

15:45.845 --> 15:48.045
     What, I can't make tea?    

15:48.080 --> 15:49.747
        We don't want to        
         touch anything         

15:49.782 --> 15:51.549
   we don't have to, remember?  
              Here.             

15:52.052 --> 15:53.618
          You got milk?         

15:55.955 --> 15:57.888
     Uh, leave it. Leave it!    

15:57.924 --> 15:59.623
 No, I've got... got gloves on. 

15:59.692 --> 16:00.891
           The power!           

16:00.927 --> 16:02.260
  But the fridge is already on. 

16:02.295 --> 16:04.228
          Mate, I'm no          
      electrician, but you      

16:04.264 --> 16:06.297
         open that door,        
       power surge, right?      

16:06.366 --> 16:08.099
        Which means spike       
       in the usage meter.      

16:08.568 --> 16:10.567
       Which means someone      
      was in an empty house     

16:10.603 --> 16:13.237
  before the deceased rocked up 
         to top himself.        

16:13.273 --> 16:14.973
            Leave it.           

16:33.959 --> 16:35.726
           [footsteps]          

16:35.761 --> 16:38.229
 You know you're not supposed to
      eat or drink in here.     

16:38.831 --> 16:40.665
    [swallows] Yeah, I know.    

16:42.802 --> 16:45.235
          [Jeff sighs]          

16:45.270 --> 16:47.138
   Do you have a single memory  

16:47.173 --> 16:48.973
       of Mum ever opening      
       or taking anything       

16:49.008 --> 16:50.775
       out of that fucking      
        crystal cabinet?        

16:52.278 --> 16:54.345
       I still get anxious      
       just being near it.      

16:55.848 --> 16:57.314
             [sighs]            

16:57.350 --> 17:01.352
    And the last time I got a   
  hiding... was in that chair.  

17:03.022 --> 17:04.488
             Really?            

17:04.522 --> 17:05.356
              Yeah.             

17:06.192 --> 17:07.525
      It was at Dad's wake.     

17:08.528 --> 17:10.294
      Cousins and strangers     
           everywhere.          

17:11.030 --> 17:13.031
 Drinkin', eatin', bullshittin'.

17:13.799 --> 17:15.366
 All I wanted was a quiet place 

17:15.367 --> 17:17.867
     to come and eat some of    
Aunty Shirl's ginger fluff cake.

17:17.936 --> 17:19.871
      I don't know how Mum      
        knew or where she       

17:19.873 --> 17:23.141
        came from, but...       
         two bites in...        

17:24.309 --> 17:25.710
  flew in like a fuckin' ninja. 

17:26.712 --> 17:29.213
     She had some kind of...    
            tripwire            

17:29.315 --> 17:31.048
         or something in        
        here, I swear it.       

17:31.050 --> 17:32.716
        [chuckles] Yeah.        

17:32.785 --> 17:34.818
 I didn't get to the third bite.

17:34.854 --> 17:35.720
             Wallop.            

17:36.623 --> 17:38.056
   Mum hit you at Dad's wake?   

17:38.691 --> 17:40.725
    Oh, yeah. A real stinger.   

17:42.194 --> 17:43.728
       I never knew that.       

17:44.864 --> 17:46.397
       Never told anyone.       

17:53.072 --> 17:55.540
         I had my first         
       kiss in this room.       

17:56.009 --> 17:57.541
         Chrissie Holt.         

17:57.576 --> 17:58.842
           [chuckles]           

17:58.877 --> 18:00.745
     Man, I was so nervous.     

18:02.414 --> 18:05.683
   I practised kissing on the   
   bathroom tiles for a week.   

18:08.754 --> 18:10.421
    I fuckin' hate this room.   

18:15.761 --> 18:16.861
            [groans]            

18:17.763 --> 18:19.063
     I'm gonna take a piss.     

18:19.699 --> 18:22.266
      Well, hang on, you...     
  you can't piss in the toilet. 

18:23.703 --> 18:24.669
           I'm sorry?           

18:26.339 --> 18:27.839
   You're fuckin' kidding me!   

18:28.941 --> 18:31.275
   - Tez, it's a septic tank.   
           - So what?           

18:31.344 --> 18:33.110
            - Water.            
        - What about it?        

18:33.179 --> 18:35.346
   The power, when you flush.   
             Surge.             

18:36.849 --> 18:39.883
Where's the power come from? You
 don't have power in a toilet!  

18:39.918 --> 18:42.286
           - The pump!          
             - Ohh!             

18:42.355 --> 18:45.055
   No, and... and you'll leave  
      residue on the bowl.      

18:45.090 --> 18:46.257
    - What does that matter?    
             - DNA.             

18:47.393 --> 18:49.126
      Yeah, but, J, we grew     
        up in this house.       

18:49.195 --> 18:51.195
      This place is riddled     
          with our DNA.         

18:51.231 --> 18:54.465
 Yeah, but... old DNA, not new. 
      There's a difference.     

18:54.934 --> 18:55.566
              What?             

18:56.636 --> 18:58.302
       So, what if I want       
         to take a shit?        

18:59.205 --> 19:01.205
        Well, unless you        
       want to poo in your      

19:01.240 --> 19:03.273
        hands and... put        
       it in your pocket,       

19:03.309 --> 19:05.276
       I suggest you hang       
       on like a big boy.       

19:07.246 --> 19:11.582
      You know, the agenda,     
  the rules, the piss bottle... 

19:11.617 --> 19:13.216
     I mean, you're starting    
         to scare me, J.        

19:13.252 --> 19:14.551
      It's like you've done     
        all this before.        

19:14.586 --> 19:16.620
      Tez, just because I'm     
       not walking around       

19:16.656 --> 19:18.589
        shivering like a        
     little frightened lamb     

19:18.624 --> 19:20.491
      doesn't mean this is      
       any easier for me.       

19:20.493 --> 19:22.927
       I mean, Jesus, the       
  worst I've ever done is a...  

19:22.962 --> 19:24.295
        dodgy tax return!       

19:24.330 --> 19:26.663
         I'm just being         
     methodical, that's all.    

19:27.333 --> 19:30.233
    It's how my brain works.    
  You'll thank me for it later. 

19:30.269 --> 19:31.836
It's how I built my business up.

19:33.238 --> 19:35.306
       What, the business       
       you sent bankrupt?       

19:36.342 --> 19:39.143
     Seriously? You're gonna    
      make today emotional?     

19:39.645 --> 19:41.178
       We're about to kill      
       our stepfather for       

19:41.180 --> 19:42.613
         a block of land        
        and an old house.       

19:42.648 --> 19:44.281
        Things are gonna        
       get pretty fucking       

19:44.317 --> 19:45.682
      emotional, J, whether     
       you like it or not.      

19:45.684 --> 19:48.586
    Well, can you just focus    
       on the job at hand?      

19:48.621 --> 19:51.255
       And we'll both get       
       emotional tomorrow.      

19:51.290 --> 19:53.457
         "Job at hand"?         

19:53.492 --> 19:54.692
              Yes!              

19:55.160 --> 19:56.694
           Oh, look...          

19:58.097 --> 19:59.797
         Think of me...         

20:00.366 --> 20:01.432
       like your foreman.       

20:01.467 --> 20:02.966
    Right? You're a brickie.    

20:03.002 --> 20:05.636
You know, when you go on a site,
     you see the framework.     

20:05.672 --> 20:09.206
    Right? It's not your job    
 to worry about the end result. 

20:09.275 --> 20:11.108
 Right? It's about the process. 

20:11.144 --> 20:12.610
        And in your case,       
         it's about the         

20:12.645 --> 20:14.445
        bricks. You worry       
        about the bricks.       

20:14.480 --> 20:15.946
   One brick after the other.   

20:15.981 --> 20:17.214
